{"nodes": [{"id": "frontend_claude_md_doc", "label": "Frontend CLAUDE.md", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_agents_md", "label": "Frontend AGENTS.md", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_proxy_ts", "label": "proxy.ts Route Guard", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Next.js 16 renamed middleware.ts/middleware() to proxy.ts/proxy(). Runs on every request except static assets; reads the jt_authed presence cookie to redirect unauthenticated users to /login and authenticated users away from public paths.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_route_groups", "label": "Route Groups (auth)/(dashboard)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_jt_authed_cookie", "label": "jt_authed Cookie", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_tokenstorage", "label": "lib/auth.ts tokenStorage", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Pure localStorage wrapper for the access token only (key jt_access). Only the Axios interceptor should read/write it. The refresh token is never stored here \u2014 it is an httpOnly cookie (jt_refresh) set by the backend, invisible to JS entirely.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_auth_store", "label": "store/auth.store.ts Zustand Store", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Persisted to localStorage under jt-auth. Central place syncing tokenStorage, the jt_authed cookie, and Zustand state.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_setauth", "label": "setAuth(user, accessToken)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Must be called after every successful login/OAuth/register \u2014 the single place that syncs tokenStorage, the jt_authed cookie (7d, SameSite=Lax), and Zustand state together.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_axios_instance", "label": "lib/api.ts Axios Instance", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Created with withCredentials:true so the browser stores and resends the jt_refresh httpOnly cookie. Request interceptor attaches Authorization: Bearer unless already set.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_response_interceptor", "label": "Response Interceptor (Refresh + Queue)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Handles concurrent 401s without duplicate refresh calls: first 401 triggers /auth/refresh, subsequent 401s queue and are stamped _retry to prevent re-entering the refresh cycle; on failure, storage/cookie are cleared and the user is redirected to /login. /auth/login and /auth/register 401s bypass this entirely.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_types_index", "label": "types/index.ts Shared Types", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_jobstatus_type", "label": "JobStatus Union Type", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_tanstack_query_conventions", "label": "TanStack Query Conventions", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "staleTime 60s, retry 1. Query key pattern by resource (['jobs',filters], ['job',id], ['job-events',id], ['resume',jobId], ['stats'], ['profile']). Mutations always invalidate related keys on success; ['resume',jobId] is updated via setQueryData instead of invalidation.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_jobform", "label": "JobForm Component", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Handles both create (POST /jobs) and edit (PATCH /jobs/:id) in one component via isEdit=!!job. On create success it stays open and renders ResumeUpload; on edit success it invalidates queries and closes immediately.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_resumeupload", "label": "ResumeUpload Component", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Renders nothing when jobId is null. Uses ['resume', jobId] with initialData from the parent so no extra network request fires on mount. Upload/remove mutations update cache via setQueryData, not invalidation. GET /jobs/resumes/file is dev-only (404 in production) so it must not be hardcoded.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_kanbanboard", "label": "KanbanBoard Component", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Fetches all jobs with limit=100 (no pagination). Shows only WISHLIST/APPLIED/INTERVIEWING/OFFER columns, intentionally excluding REJECTED/GHOSTED. Uses optimistic updates on drag with rollback on error, then invalidates on settle.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_sidebar", "label": "Sidebar Component", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Logout calls POST /auth/logout (fire-and-forget, wrapped in try/catch so a network error doesn't block client-side logout), then calls Zustand logout(), then redirects to /login.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_providers", "label": "providers.tsx", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "QueryClient is created inside useState so it stays stable across re-renders and isn't recreated every render; Toaster is placed here for global toast notifications.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_utils", "label": "lib/utils.ts Utilities", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_playwright_e2e", "label": "Playwright E2E Tests", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "frontend_claude_md_turbopack_cache_rationale", "label": "Turbopack Cache Corruption Recovery", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Endless reload loop + 'FATAL: Turbopack error'/'Next.js package not found' means the .next cache is corrupt (seen after disk I/O errors). A zombie node process still on :3000 keeps the loop alive and pushes a fresh server to :3002 where CORS/auth break, so it must be killed before deleting .next and restarting.", "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "frontend_claude_md_doc", "target": "frontend_agents_md", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "frontend_claude_md_proxy_ts", "target": "frontend_claude_md_jt_authed_cookie", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "frontend_claude_md_auth_store", "target": "frontend_claude_md_setauth", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "frontend_claude_md_setauth", "target": "frontend_claude_md_tokenstorage", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "frontend_claude_md_setauth", "target": "frontend_claude_md_jt_authed_cookie", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "frontend_claude_md_axios_instance", "target": "frontend_claude_md_response_interceptor", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "frontend_claude_md_response_interceptor", "target": "frontend_claude_md_tokenstorage", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "frontend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"s